  "summary": {
    "macroSummary": "Markets are caught between conflicting forces as Bitcoin rallies above $72K on easing Iran-Hormuz tensions while CPI data shows persistent inflation pressures that reduce rate cut odds. The geopolitical risk premium is unwinding temporarily, but fiscal data shows record tariff revenues (+272% YTD) and debt service costs approaching crisis levels at $623B YTD.",
    "regimeImpact": "The bear market relief rally assessment holds as this appears to be a geopolitical risk-off bounce rather than fundamental regime change, with underlying inflation and fiscal stress unchanged.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Maintain BMNR cash-secured put ladder with Bitcoin above $62,300 structural level and targeting $80K upside",
      "Prepare to add short exposure in software/growth names on any continued relief rally bounce",
      "Monitor HYG credit conditions closely as geopolitical premium unwinds but fiscal stress remains elevated"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Bitcoin break above $70K-$72K suggests crypto leading risk-on sentiment ahead of equities.",
      "Oil dropping on Iran talks reduces immediate stagflation pressure but Hormuz remains binary risk.",
      "CPI showing persistence keeps Fed hawkish despite one data point, rate cut odds diminishing.",
      "Record debt service costs at $623B YTD with tariff revenues spiking signals fiscal policy driving inflation."
    ]
